A clergyman, Reverend Solomon Jediel, has regained his freedom fourdays after his abduction by armed men in Taraba State.Jediel, a gospel preacher with the United Methodist church, Mallum, asuburb of Ardo-Kola Local Government Area, was kidnapped by the gunmenin the early hours of Tuesday.ChannelsTV reports that N700,000 was paid to the kidnappers before theclergyman regained his freedom.The source added that the abductors contacted the family on Saturdaymorning after paying the ransom to come and pick the victim atMararaban Mallam-Ali junction.Following his abduction, Jedielâ€™s abductors had called his family tostart saving up for his release.